<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10681265>
    dc:description "FIGURE 1. Arctosa spp. Female Arctosa conflicta sp. nov. a, c, e. Habitus with measurement patterns (a, lateral; c, frontal; e, dorsal). b, f. male palpus Arctosa villa sp. nov. (b, ventral; f, retrolateral). d. Male Arctosa tenebrosa comb. nov. Scale bars: a, c, e 2 mm; b, d, f, 0.25 mm. ANT anal tubercle, ALE anterior lateral eye, AME anterior median eye, C conductor, CH prosoma height, CL prosoma length, CW prosoma wide, CYM cymbium, DMA depression of MA, E embolus, LMB longitudinal median band, MA median apophysis, OA ocular area,Pa Posterior arm, Pp palea protuberance, PLE postero lateral eye, PME postero median eye, PSB pale submarginal band, Ra Retrolateral arm, SD seminal duct, SP spinnerets, T tegulum, TA Terminal Apophysis, ST subtegulum." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10681265/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10681275>
    dc:description "FIGURE 6. Arctosa conflicta sp. nov. Male bulb (ICN-Ar 12814) (a, ventral; b, retrolateral; c, apical. Scale bars: a–c, 200 µm. E embolus, Pa Posterior arm, Pp Palea protuberance, Ra Retrolateral arm, TA terminal apophysis." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10681275/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10681277>
    dc:description "FIGURE 7. Arctosa conflicta sp. nov. Male habitus (ICN-Ar 12814) a–c (a, dorsal; b, ventral; c, lateral), pedipalpal bulb d–g (d, ventral; e, prolateral; f, anterior; g, posterior). Scale bars: a–g, 200 µm. DMA depression of MA, E embolus, Pa posterior arm, Pp Palea protuberance, Ra retrolateral arm, SD seminal duct, ST subtegulum, TA terminal apophysis." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10681277/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10681279>
    dc:description "FIGURE 8. Arctosa conflicta sp. nov. Epigynum (MUSM-ENT 505361) a, c, d (a, ventral; c, dorsal; d, basal), prosoma, b, e (b, lateral; e, frontal) Scale bars: a, c, d, 0.25 mm, b, e, 2 mm. CO copulatory opening, FD fertilization duct, HS head of spermatheca, VC vulval chamber." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10681279/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10681281>
    dc:description "FIGURE 9. Arctosa conflicta sp. nov. Epigynum (MUSM-ENT 505361) (a, ventral; b, dorsal) Scale bars: a–b, 0.1 mm. HS head of spermatheca, SS stalk of spermatheca." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10681281/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10681283>
    dc:description "FIGURE 10. Arctosa conflicta sp. nov. Female prosoma (MUSM-ENT 505361) a, c, e (a, dorsal; c, ventral; e, lateral), female opisthosoma b, d, f (b, dorsal; d, ventral; f, lateral) Scale bars: a–f, 1 mm." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10681283/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10681287>
    dc:description "FIGURE 11. Arctosa conflicta sp. nov. Epigynum SEM (a, ventral; b, copulatory opening detail; c, conic papillae) Scale bars: a, 150 µm, b, 25 µm, c, 50 µm. CO copulatory opening, H hood, MS median septum, TS transversal septum." ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10681287/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

<http://dx.doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.10681393>
    dc:description "FIGURE 63. Geographic distribution records of Arctosa conflicta sp. nov. (red triangles)" ;
    fabio:hasRepresentation "https://zenodo.org/record/10681393/files/figure.png" ;
    a fabio:Figure .

